{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TB9koGGuN4V4MygBtzfh4D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a Python function that removes all script tags and their contents from HTML content using regex. I need to write this to a file called `candidate.py` in the current working directory.\n\nThe task is straightforward:\n1. Create a function that takes a string as input\n2. Use regex to find and remove all `<script>...</script>` tags and their contents\n3. Return the cleaned string\n\nFor this, I'll use the `re` module in Python. The regex pattern should match `<script` followed by anything until `</script>` and remove it all. I need to be careful about:\n- Case sensitivity (HTML tags are usually case-insensitive, but script tags are commonly lowercase)\n- Handling potential newlines and spaces within the tags\n- The DOTALL flag might be needed to match content that spans multiple lines\n\nA good regex pattern would be:\n`<script[^>]*>.*?</script>` with the DOTALL and IGNORECASE flags\n\nLet me write a clean, simple implementation:\n\n```python\nimport re\n\ndef remove_script_tags(html_content):\n    \"\"\"Remove all script tags and their contents from HTML content.\"\"\"\n    return re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', html_content, flags=re.DOTALL | re.IGNORECASE)\n```\n\nThis pattern:\n- `<script` - matches the opening script tag\n- `[^>]*` - matches any attributes in the script tag\n- `>` - matches the closing angle bracket\n- `.*?` - matches the content inside (non-greedy)\n- `</script>` - matches the closing tag\n- `re.DOTALL` - makes `.` match newlines\n- `re.IGNORECASE` - makes the match case-insensitive\n\nI should write this to `candidate.py` now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4660,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_inpu